Expr.name: Expr
Expr.ExprText: CASE WHEN EXTRACT( YEAR FROM "%1") = VALUEOF("%2") AND 1.0d * EXTRACT( MONTH FROM "%1") / 4 <= VALUEOF("%3") - 1 OR EXTRACT( YEAR FROM "%1") < VALUEOF("%2") THEN 'Y' ELSE 'N' END
Expr.ExprTextDesc: CASE WHEN EXTRACT( YEAR FROM "Oracle Data Warehouse"."Catalog"."dbo"."Dim_W_PRODUCT_D"."EFFECTIVE_TO_DT") = VALUEOF("Warehouse Refresh Date"."CURRENT_CALENDAR_YEAR") AND 1.0d * EXTRACT( MONTH FROM "Oracle Data Warehouse"."Catalog"."dbo"."Dim_W_PRODUCT_D"."EFFECTIVE_TO_DT") / 4 <= VALUEOF("Warehouse Refresh Date"."CURRENT_CALENDAR_QTR") - 1 OR EXTRACT( YEAR FROM "Oracle Data Warehouse"."Catalog"."dbo"."Dim_W_PRODUCT_D"."EFFECTIVE_TO_DT") < VALUEOF("Warehouse Refresh Date"."CURRENT_CALENDAR_YEAR") THEN 'Y' ELSE 'N' END

LogicalColumn.name: Product Key
LogicalColumn.Description: Uniquely identifies any goods or services procured or produced for sale, barter or internal use. This is a surrogate key assigned by Siebel Systems. It is used as a primary key.

LogicalColumn.name: Product Number
LogicalColumn.Description: This is a unique number to identify the product.

LogicalColumn.name: Product Name
LogicalColumn.Description: This is a detailed description of the product.

LogicalColumn.name: Alternate Product Number
LogicalColumn.Description: This is an alternate product number assigned to the product.

LogicalColumn.name: Universal Product Code
LogicalColumn.Description: This is the universal product code. A product can have an international article number for identification purposes.

LogicalColumn.name: Universal Product Description
LogicalColumn.Description: This is the description of the universal product code.

LogicalColumn.name: Industry Standard Description
LogicalColumn.Description: This is the description of the product in accordance with the appropriate industry standard (such as ANSI or ISO).

LogicalColumn.name: Product Type Code
LogicalColumn.Description: This code identifies the product type. Examples includes 'raw materials' 'finished goods' or ' trade'

LogicalColumn.name: Product Type Description
LogicalColumn.Description: This is the description portion of the product type code.

LogicalColumn.name: Product Group
LogicalColumn.Description: This is the product group code. Products with similar attributes can be grouped. For example, a product can belong to the chemical group, paints group or general stores. Product hierarchies can be define based on product groups.

LogicalColumn.name: Product Group Description
LogicalColumn.Description: This is the description of the product group code.

LogicalColumn.name: Basic Product
LogicalColumn.Description: This is the basic constituent of the product.

LogicalColumn.name: Product Hierarchy 1
LogicalColumn.Description: This column is provided by Siebel Systems for storing a hierarchy code.

LogicalColumn.name: Product Hierarchy 1 Name
LogicalColumn.Description: This column is provided by Siebel Systems for storing the description that corresponds to the hierarchy code.

LogicalColumn.name: Product Hierarchy 2
LogicalColumn.Description: This column is provided by Siebel Systems for storing a hierarchy code.

LogicalColumn.name: Product Hierarchy 2 Name
LogicalColumn.Description: This column is provided by Siebel Systems for storing the description that corresponds to the hierarchy code.

LogicalColumn.name: Product Hierarchy 3
LogicalColumn.Description: This column is provided by Siebel Systems for storing a hierarchy code.

LogicalColumn.name: Product Hierarchy 3 Name
LogicalColumn.Description: This column is provided by Siebel Systems for storing the description that corresponds to the hierarchy code.

LogicalColumn.name: Product Hierarchy 4
LogicalColumn.Description: This column is provided by Siebel Systems for storing a hierarchy code.

LogicalColumn.name: Product Hierarchy 4 Name
LogicalColumn.Description: This column is provided by Siebel Systems for storing the description that corresponds to the hierarchy code.

LogicalColumn.name: Product Hierarchy 5
LogicalColumn.Description: This column is provided by Siebel Systems for storing a hierarchy code.

LogicalColumn.name: Product Hierarchy 5 Name
LogicalColumn.Description: This column is provided by Siebel Systems for storing the description that corresponds to the hierarchy code.

LogicalColumn.name: Product Hierarchy 6
LogicalColumn.Description: This column is provided by Siebel Systems for storing a hierarchy code.

LogicalColumn.name: Product Hierarchy 6 Name
LogicalColumn.Description: This column is provided by Siebel Systems for storing the description that corresponds to the hierarchy code.

LogicalColumn.name: Division
LogicalColumn.Description: This code identifies the division. Products can be classified by the division code to determine their sales or business area.

LogicalColumn.name: Division Description
LogicalColumn.Description: This is the description of the division code.

LogicalColumn.name: Industry
LogicalColumn.Description: This is the industry code. This field specifies the branch of industry to which the product is assigned.

LogicalColumn.name: Industry Name
LogicalColumn.Description: This is the description of the industry code.

LogicalColumn.name: Configurable Product Flag
LogicalColumn.Description: This indicates whether the product is configurable or not.

LogicalColumn.name: Configuration Category
LogicalColumn.Description: This code identifies the configuration category.

LogicalColumn.name: Configuration Category Description
LogicalColumn.Description: This is the description of the configuration category.

LogicalColumn.name: Batch Flag
LogicalColumn.Description: This indicates whether the material is managed in batches.

LogicalColumn.name: Low Level Code
LogicalColumn.Description: This is the lowest level that a product appears in any product structure of the company.

LogicalColumn.name: Source Of Supply
LogicalColumn.Description: A field for determining any unique sources of supply for the product - internal or external.

LogicalColumn.name: Container
LogicalColumn.Description: This code identifies the container that the products are being stored.

LogicalColumn.name: Container Description
LogicalColumn.Description: This is the description of the container code that the products are being stored.

LogicalColumn.name: Storage Type
LogicalColumn.Description: This is the storage type code. This determines the product storage method. For example, products can be stored in containers, bottles, or barrels.

LogicalColumn.name: Storage Type Description
LogicalColumn.Description: This is the description of the storage type code.

LogicalColumn.name: Shipping Type
LogicalColumn.Description: This is the shipping type code. For example, the shipping type can be barrels for liquids or containers for pallets.

LogicalColumn.name: Shipping Type Description
LogicalColumn.Description: This is the description of the shipping type code. For example, the shipping type can be barrels for liquids or containers for pallets.

LogicalColumn.name: Shipping Material Group
LogicalColumn.Description: This is the shipping material type code. This code groups together products which require similar shipping materials.

LogicalColumn.name: Shipping Material Group Description
LogicalColumn.Description: This is the description of the shipping material type code. This code groups together products which require similar shipping materials.

LogicalColumn.name: Shipping Method Group
LogicalColumn.Description: This is the shipping method group code. This code groups together products which require similar shipping arrangements. For example, perishables and durables products will required two different methods of shipment.

LogicalColumn.name: Shipping Method Group Description
LogicalColumn.Description: This is the description of the shipping method group code. This code groups together products which require similar shipping arrangements. For example, perishables and durables products will required two different methods of shipment.

LogicalColumn.name: Hazardous Material Number
LogicalColumn.Description: This is the hazardous material number that identifies the material as a hazardous or dangerous.

LogicalColumn.name: Hazardous Material Description
LogicalColumn.Description: This is the description of the hazardous material number that identifies the material as a hazardous or dangerous.

LogicalColumn.name: Shelf Life
LogicalColumn.Description: This is the shelf life of the product.

LogicalColumn.name: Base UOM
LogicalColumn.Description: This is the base unit of measure code in which the product is managed.

LogicalColumn.name: Base UOM Description
LogicalColumn.Description: This is the description of the base unit of measure code in which the product is managed.

LogicalColumn.name: Sales UOM
LogicalColumn.Description: This is a sales unit of measure code to measure the product sold.

LogicalColumn.name: Sales UOM Description
LogicalColumn.Description: This is the description of the sales unit of measure code to measure the product sold.

LogicalColumn.name: UOW
LogicalColumn.Description: This is a unit of weight code to measure the product. A conversion factor allowing conversion into the base unit is defined for each unit.

LogicalColumn.name: UOW Description
LogicalColumn.Description: This is the description of the unit of weight code to measure the product.

LogicalColumn.name: Unit Gross Weight
LogicalColumn.Description: This is the gross weight of an unit of the product.

LogicalColumn.name: Unit Net Weight
LogicalColumn.Description: This is the net weight of an unit of the product.

LogicalColumn.name: UOV
LogicalColumn.Description: This is a unit of volume code to measure the product. A conversion factor allowing conversion into the base unit is defined for each unit.

LogicalColumn.name: UOV Description
LogicalColumn.Description: This is a unit of volume code to measure the product. A conversion factor allowing conversion into the base unit is defined for each unit.

LogicalColumn.name: Unit Volume
LogicalColumn.Description: This is the volume of an unit of the product.

LogicalColumn.name: Serialized Flag
LogicalColumn.Description: This flag indicates whether the product has been assigned a serial number or not. Possible values include 'Y', 'N'.

LogicalColumn.name: Serialized Count
LogicalColumn.Description: This is a count of the number of serialized components that constitute a packaged product.

LogicalColumn.name: Product Repurchase Period
LogicalColumn.Description: This is the expected period between the purchases of a product. It is used for sensitivity and profile styles of analysis. The repurchase period is stored in monthly units.

LogicalColumn.name: Product Life Cycle Stage
LogicalColumn.Description: This identifies the present stage in the life cycle of a product. Possible values for this field includes "OBSOLETE" ,"NEW" ,"MATURE" ,"WITHDRAWN", etc.

LogicalColumn.name: Product Structure Type
LogicalColumn.Description: This identifies the structure of a product. Possible values include "PACKAGE", "STANDARD".

LogicalColumn.name: Color
LogicalColumn.Description: This identifies the color of the product.

LogicalColumn.name: Brand
LogicalColumn.Description: This is the brand to which the product belongs.

LogicalColumn.name: Introduction Date
LogicalColumn.Description: This is the date when the product was introduced into the market. This column is being populated by IA_DATES.

LogicalColumn.name: Discontinuation Date
LogicalColumn.Description: This is the date on which the product was discontinued from the market.

LogicalColumn.name: Support Withdrawn Date
LogicalColumn.Description: The is the date when the support for the product was withdrawn. This column is being populated by IA_DATES.

LogicalColumn.name: Make Buy Flag
LogicalColumn.Description: This indicates whether the product is made in the organization or bought by the organization. Possible values includes 'M', 'B'.

LogicalColumn.name: Key Id
LogicalColumn.Description: This column is the unique identifier of a dimension or fact entity in its source system. In case of composite keys, the value in this column can consist of concatenated parts.

LogicalColumn.name: Source Id
LogicalColumn.Description: This column is the unique identifier of the source system from which data was extracted. In order to be able to trace the data back to its source, Siebel Systems recommends that you define separate unique source IDs for each of your different source instances.

LogicalColumn.name: Description
LogicalColumn.Description: This is a description of the product

LogicalColumn.name: Category
LogicalColumn.Description: Product Category eg High Value, Legacy fundraising, LSF Staff Led

LogicalColumn.name: Income Group
LogicalColumn.Description: Holds information on the detailed income group such as entry fees, Just giving etc

LogicalColumn.name: Type Code
LogicalColumn.Description: The product Type

LogicalColumn.name: Group Code
LogicalColumn.Description: Codes from legacy systems to represent a unique product

LogicalColumn.name: Calculation Group
LogicalColumn.Description: Manual setting of types to enable calculations. This currently only holds Cash to represent cash products
